        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies examining CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps, including the Bludszuweit power-law model calibrations from seven independent laboratories, the Goubergrits & Affeld (2004) comparative analysis, and the Fraser et al. (2012) FDA pump round-robin study. This node aggregates calibration constants, turbulence model selections, and boundary condition recommendations that collectively anchor the hemolysis power-law exponents used in the present model. The synthesis was reviewed by three independent hemolysis modeling experts and represents the consolidated state of knowledge as of 2023."
